\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 \cb2 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}4) Grab the top pointy corner of the triangle and fold it inwards by rotating it on its horizontal axis. You should now have something that looks like a triangle inside of a rectangle.\cb1 \
